    <h4>Order Workflow States</h4>
    <p>Orders have one of several workflow states and available actions to support the acquisitions workflow.</p>

    <table class="table table-striped table-bordered">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>State</th>
          <th>Available Actions</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
        <td>New</td>
        <td>Accept print, Accept no print, Temporary hold, Accept no action, Reject</td>
        <td>New is the default status for incoming orders submitted by selectors.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>MARC queue yes po</td>
        <td>Accept no action, Temp hold</td>
        <td>Orders with this status are queued for batch MARC record generation, records will print a PO when loaded into Sierra.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>MARC queue no po</td>
        <td>Accept no action, Temp hold</td>
        <td>Orders with this status are queued for batch MARC record generation, records will NOT print a PO when loaded into Sierra.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ordered</td>
        <td>Temp hold</td>
        <td>Status for orders that have been processed and officially ordered.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Waiting</td>
        <td>Accept print, Accept no print, Accept no action, Reject</td>
        <td>Use Temporary hold status to hold orders for quesons/other actions.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Rejected</td>
        <td>Temp hold</td>
        <td>Rejected status is for order requests that have been rejected.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>For administrators, each status has a list of available actions to change status.</p>
  <table class="table table-striped table-bordered">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Action</th>
        <th>Target States</th>
        <th>Notes</th>
        <tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Accept print</td>
      <td>MARC queue yes po</td>
      <td>Generate a MARC record and load with PO printing</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Accept no print</td>
      <td>MARC queue no po</td>
      <td>Generate a MARC file and load with NO po printing</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Accept no action</td>
      <td>Ordered</td>
      <td>Transition order to ordered state, no MARC record generated</td>
    </tr> 
    <tr>
      <td>Temp hold</td>
      <td>Waiting</td>
      <td>Transition record to waiting state; use this as a way to reset.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Reject</td>
      <td>Rejected</td>
      <td>Transition to rejected state</td>
    </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>


    <h4>MARC record download</h4>
    <p>Orders with a workflow state of <i>MARC queue yes po</i> or <i>MARC queue no po</i> will be processed into MARC records for loading into Sierra. Click <i>Download MARC</i> button on the index page to generate two separate MARC files: one for print PO and one for no print PO. Use the respective loaders in Sierra to input the records.</p>
